    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a preserved example of high-revving, naturally aspirated precision. Powered by the S54 3.2L inline-six, the engine features individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a linear power band up to an 8,000 RPM redline. This specimen is mechanically flawless, with the critical rear subframe reinforcement already performed and a comprehensive rod bearing service documented. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory M Variable Differential Lock. The chassis maintains its original rigidity, riding on a perfectly sorted MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension. The exterior finish and interior Nappa leather remain in showroom state, free of the typical wear found on high-mileage examples. A true turn-key investment for the discerning driver.",
